elegate to the event. The event handler is called whenever the event occurs, unless you remove the delegate. For more information about event-handler delegates, see [NIB: Events and Delegates](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/d98fd58b-fa4f-4598-8378-addf4355a115).\"\n  example:\n  - \"The following example demonstrates how to programmatically add a GridViewCancelEditEventHandler delegate to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.GridView.RowCancelingEdit> event of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.GridView> control.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[GridViewCancelEditEventHandler#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_88_1.aspx)]\\n [!code-vb[GridViewCancelEditEventHandler#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_88_1.aspx)]  \\n  \\n The following example demonstrates how to declaratively add a GridViewCancelEditEventHandler delegate to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.GridView.RowCancelingEdit> event of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.GridView> control.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[GridViewRowCancellingEdit#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_88_2.aspx)]\\n [!code-vb[GridViewRowCancellingEdit#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_88_2.aspx)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public delegate void GridViewCancelEditEventHandler(object sender, GridViewCancelEditEventArgs e);\n  inheritance:\n  - System.Delegate\n  platform:\n  - net462\nreferences:\n- uid: System.Delegate\n  isExternal: false\n  name: System.Delegate\n"}